  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support and Protection to Refugees and Asylum Seekers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- monthly cash transfers to refugees and asylum seekers
-health support to refugees and asylum seekers
-language courses for refugees and asylum seekers
-housing contracts arranged for refugees and asylum seekers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Objectives:

&#x2022;	Obj: 1. Provide vulnerable asylum-seekers and refugees in Haiti with financial assistance to cover basic needs related to health, food, and shelter. 

&#x2022;	Obj 2. Organize regular vocational training courses and weekly language (French or English) classes for interested people of concern that are offered throughout the year. 

Expected impact: 
 
o	17 identified vulnerable asylum-seekers and refugees have covered their basic needs of food, shelter, hygiene, and health covered for a year.

o	11 people complete language and/or vocational classes to improve their integration and independence in Haiti.</narrative>
  </description>
